Citation.sAbstract: Partial thermodynamic properties of Sb in liquid Ni-Sb-Sn alloys were determined by an  isopiestic vapor pressure method. Vapor pressures of Sb were measured along two sections with  constant xNi/xSn values, i.e. Ni3Sn-Sb and Ni3Sn2-Sb. Data points were obtained between  approximately 52 and 88 at% Sb in the temperature interval from 1080 to 1350 K. From these  measurements, the thermodynamic activities of Sb were calculated, and the partial molar enthalpies of  mixing of Sb were derived from their temperature dependence. The composition dependence of the Sb  activity in the two sections was calculated for 1173 K and was compared with data for the limiting  binary systems Sb-Sn and Ni-Sb.
